### BIND e EXPLAIN

```
BIND Estrategia:
  PLAN     = PLNPAY01
  PACKAGE  = PKGPAY01
  MEMBER   = PGMPAY01
  ISOLATION = CS (Cursor Stability)
  CURRENTDATA = NO (melhor performance, sem block fetch restriction)
  DEGREE   = ANY (paralelismo quando possivel)
  EXPLAIN  = YES (sempre gerar EXPLAIN)
  REOPT    = ALWAYS (reotimizar com valores reais de host variables)
```

## VSAM

### KSDS (Key Sequenced Data Set)

```
//STEP01   EXEC PGM=IDCAMS
//SYSPRINT DD SYSOUT=*
//SYSIN    DD *
  DEFINE CLUSTER -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER) -
          INDEXED -
          KEYS(10 0) -
          RECORDSIZE(200 250) -
          SHAREOPTIONS(2 3) -
          SPEED -
          FREESPACE(20 10) -
          CYLINDERS(50 10)) -
    DATA -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.DATA) -
          CONTROLINTERVALSIZE(4096)) -
    INDEX -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.INDEX) -
          CONTROLINTERVALSIZE(2048))
/*
```

### ESDS (Entry Sequenced Data Set)

```
  DEFINE CLUSTER -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.LOG) -
          NONINDEXED -
          RECORDSIZE(100 500) -
          SHAREOPTIONS(2 3) -
          CYLINDERS(100 20)) -
    DATA -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.LOG.DATA))
```

### RRDS (Relative Record Data Set)

```
  DEFINE CLUSTER -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.LOOKUP) -
          NUMBERED -
          RECORDSIZE(80 80) -
          SHAREOPTIONS(2 3) -
          TRACKS(50 10)) -
    DATA -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.LOOKUP.DATA))
```

### Alternate Index

```
  DEFINE ALTERNATEINDEX -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.AIDPT) -
          RELATE(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER) -
          KEYS(4 10) -
          RECORDSIZE(200 250) -
          UNIQUEKEY -
          UPGRADE) -
    DATA -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.AIDPT.DATA))

  DEFINE PATH -
         (NAME(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.PDEPT) -
          PATHENTRY(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.AIDPT))

  BLDINDEX -
         INDATASET(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER) -
         OUTDATASET(PROD.PAYROLL.DATA.MASTER.AIDPT)
```

## BOAS PRATICAS

- Todo SQL deve ser pensado para EXPLAIN: evite Stage 2 sempre que possivel
- Indices devem ter justificativa documentada (qual query atende?)
- VSAM FREESPACE: use 20/10 para arquivos com alta taxa de insercao
- SHAREOPTIONS: use (2,3) para acesso cross-region
- DCLGEN deve ser gerado com nomes COBOL-friendly (hifens, nao underscores)
